SIMPLE: niacinamide
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: niacinamide
<hw>niacinamide</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The amide of niacin (nicotinic
acid), called also <altname>nicotinamide</altname>. It was at one time
called <altname>vitamin B<sub>3</sub></altname>, and can function to
relieve nicotinic acid deficiency. Chemical formula
<chform>C6H6N2O</chform>, chemically it is
<chname>3-pyridinecarboxamide</chname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nicotinic acid amide, nicotinamide.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>niagara</ent>⟦br⟧
